    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Banyo?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Walkability to Banyo train station and Banyo Village, block size, and proximity to either the ACU Banyo campus or the better local school catchments are the primary value drivers in Banyo. The elevated streets around St Pius X Parish and Mary MacKillop College consistently attract a stronger family buyer pool than the flat western pockets closer to the rail corridor. Renovated post-war homes lead the suburb's price growth as buyer expectations rise.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Banyo?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Banyo homes typically sell within 20 to 40 days. The suburb is in a clear gentrification phase, with strong buyer demand spilling over from Nundah and Northgate as those suburbs become unaffordable for many family buyers. Renovated or well-presented properties on quality streets often produce competing offers within the first three weeks of campaign.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Banyo?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Banyo offers a quietly gentrifying village character with a revitalised Banyo Village strip on St Vincents Road, the Shorncliffe line train station and easy access to the Gateway Motorway and airport precinct. The suburb suits families and professionals who want a 12km CBD commute, walkable amenity and access to private schooling at St Pius X, Mary MacKillop College and the nearby St Joseph's Nudgee College precinct.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Banyo a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Banyo is one of the most active gentrification stories on the northside. Families and upgraders priced out of Nundah and Northgate are increasingly choosing Banyo for better block sizes at meaningfully lower entry prices, and the Banyo Village retail revival has accelerated that shift. Combined with the Shorncliffe line train station, the ACU campus and the airport employment corridor, the underlying demand fundamentals continue to support steady price growth.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

